    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/valresult/force-at-40mm",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Force at 40 mm displacement QoI comparison — primary outcome measure across both laboratories",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/data/bench-test-lab1-n6",
      "description": "The FEA ensemble (three independent model implementations: FDA in-house Abaqus model, Ansys Mechanical reference model, and DePuy Synthes proprietary solver) was run against all 11 physical constructs tested under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending loading at 5 mm/min crosshead speed. Predicted force at 40 mm displacement was extracted from each simulation's load-displacement curve at the 40 mm landmark. Experimental values were obtained from certified load-cell and crosshead-displacement channels, corrected for machine compliance using a rigid-body calibration fixture. The ensemble mean prediction fell within 6.3% of the experimental grand mean (95% CI: 4.1–8.5%), and the validation metric E/uval = 1.41 satisfied the pre-specified acceptance criterion of E/uval < 1.96. Inter-laboratory variability was 2.1% CV, confirming reproducibility. All three FEA implementations agreed within 1.8% of each other, demonstrating solver independence. This result is the primary evidence supporting the credibility claim for the non-cannulated design."
    }
  ],
