      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastic-plastic constitutive model appropriate for Ti-6Al-4V under quasi-static loading; contact formulation captures screw-rod interface behavior.",
      "rationale": "Isotropic elastic-plastic (bilinear kinematic hardening) model for Ti-6Al-4V is well-established for quasi-static spinal implant simulations. Penalty-based frictionless contact at screw-rod interface is consistent with lubricated test conditions. Geometric nonlinearity (NLGEOM) enabled to capture large-displacement response. Model form uncertainty assessed as low for this loading regime."
