    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved level 1 vs. required level 2) is accepted on the basis of well-established rate insensitivity of Ti-6Al-4V under quasi-static loading and the documented inter-laboratory reproducibility of results. All three primary QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%). The FEA ensemble demonstrates solver independence within 1.8%. The credibility evidence is sufficient to support regulatory use of the model predictions for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw compression-bending COU.",
